pizza: toppings such as cheese, pepperoni, vegetables, etc.
pot pie: a filling of savory vegetables and/or meat
red wine: a label with the name of the wine
espresso: a layer of crema on top of the espresso
tea cup: a curved spout on the other side
cliff: a sharp drop off at the edge
coral reef: bright and vibrant colors of the coral and other organisms
geyser: a pool of bubbling water at the base of the geyser
lakeshore: trees, shrubs, and other vegetation growing near the shoreline
rocks, sand, and other debris along the shoreline
beach: a horizon line with the sky and sea merging together
shells, rocks, and driftwood scattered along the shoreline
valley: a river or stream running through the valley
volcano: a plume of smoke or ash rising from the crater
baseball player: a jersey with a team logo
scuba diver: a diver carrying a tank of air on their back
a diver with a mask and snorkel
yellow lady's slipper: a long, thin stem with a single flower at the end
corn: long, green husks with silky threads
horse chestnut seed: a large, round seed with a light-colored, star-shaped pattern on the surface
agaric: gills on the underside of the cap
a stem that is usually white or off-white in color
gyromitra: a thick, fleshy stem with a white interior
earth star fungus: a central spore sac surrounded by the arms
hen of the woods mushroom: a white, spongy underside with white pores
bolete: a yellow, orange, or red coloration on the cap
corn cob: husks or leaves wrapping around the cob
